Compensation as of Fiscal Year 2017. 

SLS Capital Management, LLC Key Developments

Abercrombie To Pursue Options
Jul 18 17
SLS Capital Management, LLC has issued a letter to Board of Directors of Abercrombie & Fitch Co. (NYSE:ANF) identifying steps to maximize value for the shareholders. SLS has identified two options. Option A is a large one-time buyback in conjunction with a reduction in dividend. Option B is a monetization of assets. Option A includes initiating a Dutch tender to buy back $200 million of Abercrombie stock. At current prices this represents over 30% of shares outstanding and reduce the dividend to $0.18 per year or around a 2% dividend yield. Option B includes monetize Abercrombie's non-core assets and use the proceeds to repurchase shares.


